race.comment: Onto the Geelong Classic where we see some Victoria Derby hopefuls. AZAZEL (4) is the one that looks most suited getting to a trip. He was there to be beaten on debut but just kept grinding away before a similar run when 4th in the Super Impose at Flemington, boxing on for a narrow defeat. Drawn well, he'll land in the first few and can stake his claim for the classic. Very wary of MATSUDA (3) who was dominant in fast time at Sale, scoring by five lengths. Forgive his run two back in the Derby Preview at Flemington when copping interference. HIGHVOL (1) can improve up in trip. The run in the G2 Stutt Stakes was good for a horse on a Derby path, then he just had no hope drawing wide in the Caulfield Guineas. DON'T DOUBT DARE (16) could be sharp improver out of a farcically run debut in the Oaks Preview.
